Eclipse Setup

* Overview

  This document explains how to set up your development environment to 
  develop the <<maven-sar-plugin>> itself. While these instructions may
  be useful for developing other software, none of the things mentioned 
  on this page are required to develop software which uses the
  <<maven-sar-plugin>>.

* Install the Subclipse Plugin

   * Go to <Help> -\> <Software Updates> -\> <Find and Install>...
   
   * Choose <Search for new features to install> and click <Next>
   
   * Click on the <New Remote Site...> button.

+-----------------+
Name: Subclipse 1.2.x (Eclipse 3.2+)
URL:  http://subclipse.tigris.org/update_1.2.x
+-----------------+

   * Click <Finish>
   
   * Check <Subclipse> and click <next>
   
   * Accept the license agreement
   
   * Click <Finish>
   
   * Click <Install All>
   
   * Restart Eclipse

* Install the Maven Plugin

   * Go to <Help> -\> <Software Updates> -\> <Find and Install>...
   
   * Choose <Search for new features to install> and click <Next>
   
   * Click on the <New Remote Site...> button.

+-----------------+
Name: m2eclipse-dev
URL:  http://m2eclipse.codehaus.org/update-dev/
+-----------------+

   * Click <Finish>
   
   * Expand the <m2eclipse-dev> list
   
   * Check <Maven 2.0 Integration> and click <next>
   
   * Accept the license agreement
   
   * Click <Finish>
   
   * Click <Install All>
   
   * Restart Eclipse
   
* Import the Project

   * Right click anywhere inside the <Package Explorer> panel.
   
   * Select <Import...>
   
   * Choose <Other> -\> <Checkout Projects from SVN>
   
   * Click <Next \>>
   
   * Select <Create a new repository location>
   
   * Click <Next \>>
   
   * Enter <<https://maven-sar.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/maven-sar>>
   
   * Click <Next \>>
   
   * Select <trunk>
   
   * Click <Next \>>
   
   * Click <Finish>

* Enable Maven Dependency Management

   * Right click on the project (the <maven-sar-plugin [trunk]> title)
   
   * Choose <Maven> -\> <Enable Dependency Management>

* Import Code Formatter Profile

   * Download {{{eclipse-code-formatter.xml}eclipse-code-formatter.xml}}

   * Go to <Window> -\> <Preferences>
   
   * Drill down to <Java> -\> <Code Style> -\> <Formatter>
   
   * Click <Import...>
   
   * Browse to the location where you downloaded <eclipse-code-formatter.xml>
   
   * Click <Apply>
   
   * Click <OK>
   
